1
00:00:10,469 --> 00:00:12,972
这是一所军事学院
<font color="#808080">THOMAS LASKY:</font> This is a military academy.

2
00:00:13,055 --> 00:00:15,099
他们在教我们，嗯，如何打仗
They're, uh, teaching us how to fight.

3
00:00:18,644 --> 00:00:21,063
我的哥哥，是这里毕业的
My older brother, he trained here.

4
00:00:21,147 --> 00:00:22,565
你知道，他很优秀的
You know, he was quite popular.

5
00:00:22,648 --> 00:00:24,567
他是很多老师最喜欢的学生
He was a lot of the teachers' favorites.

6
00:00:26,610 --> 00:00:28,571
有时候我觉得很孤独
<font color="#808080">MICHAEL SULLIVAN:</font> There are times I do get lonely,

7
00:00:28,654 --> 00:00:31,240
但我也交了一些朋友
but I made a couple friends.

8
00:00:32,491 --> 00:00:34,076
社交方面，我觉得
<font color="#808080">WALTER VICKERS:</font> Socially, I don't think

9
00:00:34,160 --> 00:00:37,163
我还没适应过来
I fit in all too well.

10
00:00:41,792 --> 00:00:46,172
我叫托马斯·拉斯基，我是初级学员
My name is Thomas Lasky, and I'm a Cadet Freshman.

11
00:00:46,255 --> 00:00:48,215
在这所学院受训很辛苦
The Academy's tough in itself.

12
00:00:48,299 --> 00:00:50,885
学业要求严格，气氛也非常严肃
It's such a strict and hostile environment.

13
00:00:50,968 --> 00:00:53,137
我们正在学习如何在一场战斗中
We're trying to learn how to go in and battle

14
00:00:53,220 --> 00:00:56,098
有效地消灭敌人
and essentially kill somebody.

15
00:00:56,182 --> 00:01:00,269
我叫迈克尔·苏利文，我是初级学员
My name is Michael Sullivan, and I'm a Freshman Cadet.

16
00:01:00,352 --> 00:01:04,356
我们受训是为了与叛军作战
We're training to fight insurrectionists.

17
00:01:04,440 --> 00:01:08,152
我想我是在追随我父亲的足迹
I guess I'm following the footsteps of my dad.

18
00:01:08,235 --> 00:01:10,196
至少我是这么想的，我从没见过他
At least I think so. I've never met him.

19
00:01:10,279 --> 00:01:14,325
我爸爸是梅瑟利武器公司的首席财务官
<font color="#808080">WALTER:</font> My father is a chief financial advisor

20
00:01:14,408 --> 00:01:16,160
我是注定要来到这里的
at Mezriah Weapons.

21
00:01:14,408 --> 00:01:16,160
I was always supposed to come here.

22
00:01:16,243 --> 00:01:20,331
这都是家里为我计划好的
It was always something that had been planned for me.

23
00:01:20,414 --> 00:01:23,209
我叫沃特·韦克斯，初级学员
Walter Vickers, Freshman Cadet.

24
00:01:24,585 --> 00:01:26,045
我叫艾普莉·奥瑞斯基
My name is April Orenski.

25
00:01:26,128 --> 00:01:27,463
我是高级学员
I am a Senior Cadet.

26
00:01:27,546 --> 00:01:29,423
我是哈斯塔提小队的队长
I am the squad leader for Hastati Squad.

27
00:01:30,466 --> 00:01:33,844
我很希望能够在UNSC的军队里找到自己的位置
I was really looking for a place where I can serve the UNSC,

28
00:01:33,928 --> 00:01:36,055
科布罗学院是最好的军校
and Corbulo Academy is the best.

29
00:01:38,057 --> 00:01:39,809
一切对我来说都很新鲜
I'm so new to everything.

30
00:01:39,892 --> 00:01:41,894
你看，我不是在这种环境下长大的
You know, I wasn't raised in this kind of environment,

31
00:01:41,977 --> 00:01:43,354
我还在适应着这一切…
so I'm still trying to...

32
00:01:43,437 --> 00:01:45,189
我试着融入这个环境
I'm trying to fit in.

33
00:01:46,315 --> 00:01:47,775
我叫陈俊杰
My name is JunJie Chen.

34
00:01:47,858 --> 00:01:49,318
我是初级学员
I'm a Freshman Cadet.

35
00:01:49,401 --> 00:01:52,947
我叫凯勒·席尔瓦，我是初级学员
I'm Chyler Silva, and I'm a Freshman Cadet

36
00:01:53,030 --> 00:01:55,116
刚刚加入科布罗军事科学学院
at Corbulo Academy of Military Science.

37
00:01:56,200 --> 00:02:00,246
我好像一直都想加入军队
I sort of always knew that I wanted to be military.

38
00:02:00,329 --> 00:02:02,456
在我10岁的时候，我妈妈就教我如何端起步枪
My mum taught me how to hold a rifle when I was 10.

39
00:02:03,415 --> 00:02:08,003
这里的训练，是我未来人生规划的一部分
<font color="#808080">DIMAH TCHAKOVA:</font> This training, it's part of who I am about to become.

40
00:02:08,087 --> 00:02:10,714
我必须做该做的事情，走在人生的前面
I have to do what I have to do to get ahead in life.

41
00:02:11,632 --> 00:02:13,384
我叫迪玛·切科娃
My name is Dimah Tchakova.

42
00:02:13,467 --> 00:02:15,386
我是初级学员
I'm Freshman Cadet.

43
00:02:16,470 --> 00:02:21,851
挺辛苦的，但我想，这种团队式的训练会有帮助吧
<font color="#808080">SULLY:</font> It's been kind of hard, but I think structure guides people.

44
00:02:22,893 --> 00:02:24,728
我想是很难，但太艰苦？
<font color="#808080">WALTER:</font> I think it's hard, but too severe?

45
00:02:24,812 --> 00:02:27,189
不，我觉得还不是太艰苦
No, I don't think it's too severe.

46
00:02:27,273 --> 00:02:28,732
如果要说的话，就是还不够艰苦
If anything, it's not severe enough,

47
00:02:28,816 --> 00:02:30,484
而且我们在战争中处于劣势
and I don't think we're winning,

48
00:02:30,568 --> 00:02:33,404
我想我们需要竭尽全力、不择手段去争取胜利
and I think we need to do everything possible to win.

49
00:02:34,530 --> 00:02:36,031
这不是游戏
<font color="#808080">CHYLER:</font> It's not a game.

50
00:02:36,115 --> 00:02:37,825
是让你活下来的训练
It's training for life.

51
00:02:37,908 --> 00:02:40,786
我必须做到最好，因为我相信能够赢得这场战争
I need to be good at this, because I believe in this war.

52
00:02:41,996 --> 00:02:44,623
我开始想我们能否简单地解决这些问题
<font color="#808080">THOMAS:</font> I'm starting to think that we could sort these things out

53
00:02:44,707 --> 00:02:46,917
而不必去打仗，去杀害那些无辜的人
without going into battle and killing innocent people.

54
00:02:47,001 --> 00:02:49,461
但在学校我不能说那样的话
I can't really say stuff like that at this school,

55
00:02:49,545 --> 00:02:51,088
因为那样做大家都会笑话我的
because people kind of laugh at me,

56
00:02:51,172 --> 00:02:53,382
而且他们会欺负我
and they kind of bully me a bit.

57
00:02:53,465 --> 00:02:55,217
我对叛军怎么看？
<font color="#808080">WALTER:</font> What do I think of the insurrectionists?

58
00:02:56,510 --> 00:02:57,845
我想他们都是自私的人
I think they're selfish.

59
00:02:57,928 --> 00:03:01,265
屠杀那些手无寸铁的人是不对的
You don't kill people who aren't even fighting.

60
00:02:59,847 --> 00:03:01,265
It's not right.

61
00:03:02,808 --> 00:03:04,685
我就是在叛军一次又一次的袭击中长大的
<font color="#808080">CHYLER:</font> I grew up around a lot of Innie violence,

62
00:03:04,768 --> 00:03:09,356
他们的目标不仅仅是军事目标
and not just violence towards military targets.

63
00:03:09,440 --> 00:03:12,276
我那里的平民们都不得不学会保护自己
Civilians where I lived really had to learn how to protect themselves.

64
00:03:12,359 --> 00:03:15,529
作为队长意味着我是他们的领袖
<font color="#808080">APRIL:</font> Being a squad leader means I am their leader.

65
00:03:15,613 --> 00:03:17,489
我要为他们负责
I'm responsible for them.

66
00:03:20,409 --> 00:03:23,871
在背后，他们叫我「机器人」，不过我不介意
They call me "The Robot" behind my back, but I don't mind.

67
00:03:23,954 --> 00:03:25,791
能以一个科布罗学员、一个UNSC战士的方式来做事
I'm proud to do things the Corbulo way, the UNSC way.

68
00:03:25,792 --> 00:03:27,791
我感到很骄傲

69
00:03:29,835 --> 00:03:30,961
我觉得我们不是一定要适应环境的
<font color="#808080">WALTER:</font> I don't think we're supposed to fit in

70
00:03:31,045 --> 00:03:32,296
或者一定要交朋友
or necessarily make friends,

71
00:03:32,379 --> 00:03:34,215
我们只要团结一致、努力训练
as long as we work together and we work hard

72
00:03:34,298 --> 00:03:35,674
完成肩负的使命即可
and we do what we're supposed to do.

73
00:03:35,758 --> 00:03:37,343
如果是那样的话，我觉得我还算适应的
In that sense, I feel like I fit in great.

74
00:03:37,426 --> 00:03:41,180
我觉得我注定要来到这里
I feel like I'm meant to be here.

75
00:03:41,263 --> 00:03:44,266
我哥哥一直认为我会成为一名优秀的士兵
<font color="#808080">THOMAS:</font> My brother always thought I'd be a good soldier.

76
00:03:44,350 --> 00:03:48,062
作为一名士兵，并不是毫无原则地使用暴力
<font color="#808080">CHYLER:</font> Being a soldier isn't about mindless violence.

77
00:03:48,145 --> 00:03:49,355
你需要清醒的头脑
You need a clear head,

78
00:03:49,438 --> 00:03:53,150
谈到叛军，杀戮只是一部分
and given the insurrectionists, killing is part of that.

79
00:03:53,275 --> 00:03:55,444
我能够下手杀人么？
<font color="#808080">SULLY:</font> Would I be able to take another life?

80
00:03:55,527 --> 00:03:57,446
能吧，我能下手杀人的
<font color="#808080">WALTER:</font> Yeah, I'd be able to kill.

81
00:03:57,529 --> 00:03:59,615
毕竟，不是你杀人就是被人杀
After all, it's kill or be killed.

82
00:03:59,698 --> 00:04:02,117
我真的觉得自己还没有准备好去打仗
<font color="#808080">THOMAS:</font> I don't really feel like I'm ready to go into battle.

83
00:04:05,496 --> 00:04:09,333
我想我根本就杀不了人
I don't think I could kill another human being ever.

